    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-02-06T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-02-06T15:00:00-05:00" n="544"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d544">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.248/2–645: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Butterworth</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-02-06T21:00:00+01:00"
                            >February 6, 1945—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received February 7—11:02 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>276. For Hickerson<note n="81" xml:id="d544fn81">John D, Hickerson, Deputy
                        Director, Office of European Affairs.</note> and Culbertson.<note n="82"
                        xml:id="d544fn82">Paul T, Culbertson, Chief, Division of Western European
                        Affairs.</note> After several meetings attended by George, Payne, Haering
                    and Bond with the Spanish delegation the following definite proposal was finally
                    obtained from the Spanish Government. As translated it reads:</p>
                <p>[Here follows text as in protocol effected by exchange of notes, February 19,
                    printed on <ref target="#pg_727">pages 727</ref>–<ref target="#pg_730"
                    >730</ref>, except that in final text article V was added and articles V to XI
                    of this draft were accordingly renumbered.]</p>
                <p>Pertinent comment will follow.</p>
                <p>George and Payne left for Lisbon tonight.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Butterworth</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
